DATA CLOUD
Unlock Hidden Insights with Tableau

After you’ve combined, unified, and harmonized your data in Data Cloud, it’s now ready for you to analyze. Use Tableau to find useful and actionable insights that can drive business success and create a personalized experience for your customers. Data Cloud, Tableau, and Salesforce 360 apps work together to consolidate your data and create a single customer record. Unlock hidden insights, and make decisions based on all your customer data.

With Data Cloud and Tableau, you can:

Connect Tableau to Data Cloud data model objects using the built-in Salesforce Data Cloud connector in Tableau.
Analyze your data in near real time with a live connection to Data Cloud.
Quickly analyze your data with the Salesforce purpose-built Accelerator dashboards.
Create key metrics that drive your business decisions.
Publish the metrics to Tableau Cloud or Tableau Server to share with your colleagues.
Make the metrics available to your decision-makers in their workflow, and embed your metrics and dashboards in your Salesforce instance.
What You Need
Data Cloud Starter pack
Tableau Creator license to connect to Data Cloud and author views and dashboards and embed them in your Salesforce instance
Tableau explorer or viewer licenses for accessing the views and dashboards in Tableau

To learn more about Tableau licenses, see Understanding Role-Based License Model.

Connect Tableau in Data Cloud
Set up a connection to Data Cloud from Tableau. Different steps are required depending on which Tableau product and version you use.
Enable Data Cloud in Tableau
Using the Data Cloud connector, you can discover and analyze unified profiles and other customer insights.
Use Data Cloud Data in Tableau
Tableau enables metadata and data discovery of all objects in your Data Cloud instance with Salesforce security mode.
Use Data Cloud Data Spaces to Organize Data in Tableau
Use data spaces to segregate your data, metadata, and processes into categories, such as brand, region, or department. Set up permissions so that users can see and work on data only in the context of their brand or region.
View Tableau Dashboards
After defining visualizations on your Data Cloud data in Tableau, you can view these dashboards by embedding or publishing them.
Visual Segment Creation to Data Cloud
Segmentation enables data analysts to curate relevant portions of data from their analyses in Tableau and seamlessly transfer them as segments to Data Cloud.
Tableau Accelerators for Data Cloud
A Tableau accelerator provides ready-to-use dashboards and workbooks geared for a particular industry or business use case. All Tableau accelerators use the Salesforce Data Cloud connector to connect Tableau and Data Cloud.
Data Cloud and Tableau Use Cases
Tableau helps you explore, analyze, and find hidden insights in your data. The Tableau to Data Cloud connectors use the Hyper query engine to provide fast processing. You can explore your Data Cloud data in near real time enabling quick and accurate decision-making. These example use cases illustrate how Data Cloud and Tableau work together to help you achieve your business goals and deliver a personalized experience for your customers.
